        "pairingText": "Hot Dogs on the menu? Try pairing with Riesling, Gewurztraminer, and ros Wine. A Gewrztraminer will be great with your basic New York style hot dog with mustard and sauerkraut. For a Chicago-style dog with sour pickles and hot peppers, you might opt for a crisp Riesling. No matter your toppings, a dry ros almost always works. The Snoqualmie Naked Riesling with a 4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 11 dollars per bottle.",
