      "instructions": "In a large bowl, mix together meat and seasonings. Let the meat mixture rest for 3 hours, up to overnight.When you are ready to grill your burgers, preheat your grill to medium high. (You should be able to hold your hand a few inches from the cooking grate for 6-7 seconds.)Divide the meat into 8 roughly even sections and shape them into patties slightly larger than your bun. (The pork will shrink a bit as it cooks.)Grill the burgers for roughly 4 minutes per side, until they are firm and cooked through.Serve the brat burgers on a bun with sauerkraut and mustard, if thats your thing. If not, theyre just as good with ketchup, or any other burger topping for that matter.",
