      "instructions": "Preparation                                                        Preheat oven to 425. Toss orange and lemon slices with 1 tablespoon oil on a rimmed baking sheet; season with salt and pepper. Roast citrus, tossing occasionally, until lightly charred in spots and starting to caramelize, 10-15 minutes. This makes the citrus flavor more complex. Let cool.                                                                Meanwhile, combine onion and lemon juice in a large bowl; season with salt and pepper and let sit 5 minutes (onion will soften a bit and get slightly sweeter and less harsh).                                                                Add roasted citrus to bowl with onion along with arugula and mint. Drizzle remaining 3 tablespoons oil over; season with salt and pepper and toss everything to combine and coat.                                                                Add avocado and very gently toss until lightly dressed (you don't want to crush the avocado).                                                                         Calories 260 - Fat 22 g - Fiber 6 g                            Nutritional analysis provided by                                        Bon Apptit",
