      "instructions": "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or silicone baking mat. Set aside.Cream butter with electric mixer for 30 seconds. Add both sugars and cream until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes.Add egg and vanilla and beat until smooth.In a large mixing bow, whisk together flour, soda and salt. Add the dry ingredients to the butter mixture and mix on low just until combined. Add the white chocolate and cranberries and stir it in.Scoop the cookie dough onto the prepared baking sheet using a cookie scoop. (I used 1,5\" cookie scoop).Bake cookies for 8 to 10 minutes or until the edges start to brown. The cookies will look underdone in the center but they will set as they cool.Cool on the sheet for 2 minutes, transfer onto a cooling rack.Store in cookie jar (or covered container) for up to 5 days.",
