      "instructions": "Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. add the onion, carrots, ginger, cumin and 1 tsp salt. Cook, stirring frequently, about 6 minutes. Add 4 cups of water and bring to a boil. Lower to a simmer, and cook, covered for about 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.While the soup is cooking, remove the collard leaves from the stems. Roll them up and then cut them into thin strips. Put the strips in a second pot with 1/2 cup water and a pinch of salt. Steam until tender, about 4-5 minutes. Drain and toss with the coconut butter and lime juice. Season with salt to taste.When the soup is ready, puree it until smooth. Season to taste with salt. Serve topped with collard greens and a sprinkle of Dukkah.Heat the oven to 350.Spread the pistachios, sesame seeds, coriander seeds, and cumin seeds in a baking pan. Toast until fragrant, about 8 minutes. Let cool for a few minutes.Transfer the nuts and seeds, thyme oregano, and 3/4 tsp salt to a food processor. Pulse until roughly ground but still crunchy. Season with pepper.",
